    "steps": [
        "Rinse White Rice until water runs somewhat clear through it",
        "Put Rice in pot w/ 4 Cups of Water",
        "Add 1 teaspoon of Salt, and put on medium-high heat for 20 min",
        "In a wide stovetop pan, put Vegetable Oil on medium-high heat",
        "Add Onion, stir as it fries until translucent (~4 minutes)",
        "Briefly toast Garam Masala, then stir into the onion",
        "Stir in Tomato Paste for about 30 seconds",
        "Stir in Paprika, Ground Cayenne, and Ginger-Garlic Paste",
        "Lower heat a bit (maybe just high of medium) and keep stirring",
        "After a minute, add the can of Ground Peeled Tomatoes",
        "Stir and let reduce for 10 minutes",
        "Break Tandoori Chicken down into big chunks (with your hands)",
        "Stir in Heavy Cream, 2 Cups of Water, 1/4 tsp Salt, and Sugar",
        "Let everything heat up in the pan, then serve with Rice"
